tion of an independent panel, in order to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ensure it did not fall too </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">far behind </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">other CEOs in the sector</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In much the same way that Catholic schools do not want to undermine purpose of ensuring that young people get a good Catholic education by insisting that the teachers and head-teachers working in those schools should be</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> paid less than their counterparts at secul</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ar or other faith-based schools –</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and therefore risk </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">losing many of the best of them – we have to ensure we </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">strike an appropriate balance</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in relation to the rest of the sector.</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Beyond the Director, the same car</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">eful approach is taken to salary levels throughout the organisation.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">For</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> senior management, the number of people earning more than £60,000 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">currently stands at six, and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">not risen in recent years. In addition to the Director, these individuals are the o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ther members of CAFOD’s Leadership Team: the heads of our (i) International, (ii) Finance, (iii) Advocacy and Communications, (iv) Communities and Supporters; and (v) Organisational Development and People, divisions.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">These are difficult balances to strike.  Issues around CEO salaries in any sector can be contentious and occasionally the subject of media attention.  As an agency that is guided by Catholic values in all it does, CAFOD </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">works hard to strike a balance that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">upholds these</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> values and is acceptable to our supporters.  As Bishop John Arnold, Chair of Trustees says: “</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e are honoured to make our contribution to this organisation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">take this responsibility very seriously”.  CAFOD </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">goes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> beyond the basic requirement</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s of transparency in all aspect</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s of our financial arrangements, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">seeking to set an example.  We will continue in this spirit and wish the Committee well in its work.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">CAFOD would be happy to provide any further information required by the Committee.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>